@@ -4,14 +4,16 @@
 - Branch: `feat/bldicons-20260531`
 - Files reviewed: `src/Runtime/UI/CanvasReskinner.cs`, `src/Runtime/UI/NativeMenuInjector.cs`, `src/Runtime/UI/NativeUiHelper.cs`, `src/Runtime/UI/ModMenuPanel.cs`
 - No active sprite-null assignments were found in `CanvasReskinner.cs` and `ModMenuPanel.cs`.
-- In `NativeUiHelper.CopySelectableVisualState`, we found an unconditional assignment that could clear visuals:
-  - `src/Runtime/UI/NativeUiHelper.cs:245` → `resolvedImage.sprite = donorImage.sprite;`
-- In `NativeMenuInjector.CopyImageVisualStyle`, we found another unconditional assignment that could clear visuals:
-  - `src/Runtime/UI/NativeMenuInjector.cs:1696` → `target.sprite = source.sprite;`
+- In `NativeMenuInjector`'s target-graphic fallback, we found a replacement that could point a button at an empty graphic:
+  - `src/Runtime/UI/NativeMenuInjector.cs:687` → `modsButton.targetGraphic = fallbackImage;` when the fallback image had no sprite.
+- In `NativeUiHelper.CopySelectableVisualState`, the sprite copy is already guarded and now preserves the existing native sprite when the donor has none:
+  - `src/Runtime/UI/NativeUiHelper.cs:245` → `if (donorImage.sprite != null) { resolvedImage.sprite = donorImage.sprite; }`
+- In `NativeMenuInjector.CopyImageVisualStyle`, the sprite copy is also guarded:
+  - `src/Runtime/UI/NativeMenuInjector.cs:1696` → `if (source.sprite != null) { target.sprite = source.sprite; }`
 
 ## Fix
-- Guarded both sprite copies to only write when the donor sprite is non-null.
-- This keeps existing cloned/background sprites intact when source sprites are missing.
+- Guarded the target-graphic fallback so we only swap in a replacement when it actually has a sprite.
+- Kept the existing guard in the sprite-copy helpers so donor-null sprites never overwrite a live native image.
 - If a donor sprite is available, existing copy behavior remains unchanged.
 
 ## Build status
